A rare food & beverage opportunity now exists at Mile End Homemaker Centre. CBRE are delighted to bring the only retail café opportunity within the centre to the market for lease.

The opportunity consists of 150 sqm of space adjoining Subway located in the central retail hub of the development. The tenancy, currently trading as a café, comprises of mainly open plan seating with a counter, kitchen and storage back of house.

An incoming tenant can benefit from the existing infrastructure, customer base and captured market from the centres employees.

Mile End is the largest Homemaker Centre in central Adelaide located just 3km from the CBD. Fully leased the centre is anchored by major national large format tenants such as The Goodguys, Annaconda, Nick Scali and also home to Australia’s best performing Adairs.

This metropolitan centre comprises of 33,981 sqm of GLA with 34 tenants and 94% being national retailers.
The catchment area of 473,321 people is forecast to grow by 7.0% over next 8 years, fuelled by apartment growth within Adelaide’s CBD. The centre is the largest LFR centre in central Adelaide and has benefited from the high average spend per capita on LFR goods, 6.4% above the Adelaide average.
